The Borno Ministry of Education has begun ‘Learn at Home Programme’  for students preparing for West African Senior School Certificate  Examination (WASSCE). A statement by the Commissioner for Education, Alhaji Bello Ayuba
said the programme is through the media involving radio and television
stations in the state as well as social media. Ayuba explained that the programme involved selected teachers, who would teach for 45 minutes per lesson. He said subjects to be taught from Monday to Friday include
Mathematics, English, Biology, Physics, Chemistry, Religion, Economics
and civil Education. The commissioner added that the subjects would be taught via
broadcast stations like NTA Maiduguri, Borno Radio/Television, Dandal
Kura Radio and Peace FM. In another development, the restriction of movement in and out of Borno was being enforced. NAN reports that the restriction was part of precautionary measures by the state against the spread of COVID-19. The State Deputy Governor, who is also the Chairman, High Powered
Response Team on COVID-19, Alhaji Umar Kadafur, made this known in a
statement. He said only those on essential duties and vehicles carrying food
items, petrol, drugs, and other essential commodities would be allowed
into the state. (NAN) Suleiman idris is a graduate of Fed Univ of Tech Minna (BTECH Mathematics/Comp Science), Specialist in ICT Support Services. also proficient in use of  online journalism tools & Social media management.  I currently serve as I.T Officer with Africa's Largest TV Network NTA